11 An Act relating to definitions and general
provisions; enacting the United States and Oklahoma
12 Flag Display Rights Act of 2025; prohibiting state or
local government entities from restricting persons
13 from making proper display of the flag of the United
States of America or the flag of the State of
14 Oklahoma; providing for noncodification; providing
for codification; and declaring an emergency.
15
16
17 BE IT ENACTED BY THE PEOPLE OF THE STATE OF OKLAHOMA:
18 SECTION 1. NEW LAW A new section of law not to be
19 codified in the Oklahoma Statutes reads as follows:
20 This act shall be known and may be cited as the "United States
21 and Oklahoma Flag Display Rights Act of 2025".
22 SECTION 2. NEW LAW A new section of law to be codified
23 in the Oklahoma Statutes as Section 155.1 of Title 25, unless there
24 is created a duplication in numbering, reads as follows:
HB1776 HFLR Page 1
BOLD FACE denotes Committee Amendments.

1 A. No state or local government entity shall prohibit any
2 person from displaying either the flag of the United States of
3 America or the flag of the State of Oklahoma on property owned by or
4 lawfully occupied by such state or local government entity if the
5 display is made from a vehicle owned by or lawfully operated by such
6 person or if the display is being made by the person holding the
7 flag whether or not the display is made from a vehicle and if the
8 flag is being displayed in accordance with accepted standards for
9 the proper and respectful display of such flag and the flag has not
10 been altered or modified or defaced in any way.
11 B. The provisions of this section shall be applicable to a
12 motorcycle owned or lawfully operated by such person or any other
13 vehicle authorized pursuant to law to be operated on public roads or
14 highways.
15 SECTION 3. It being immediately necessary for the preservation
16 of the public peace, health or safety, an emergency is hereby
17 declared to exist, by reason whereof this act shall take effect and
18 be in full force from and after its passage and approval.
